The International Center for Policy and Conflict yesterday asked political parties and hopefuls to focus on issue-based campaigns.Executive director Wainaina Ndung&rsquo;u urged voters to elect leaders who give priority to security, economy, equality and job creation.&rdquo;We underscore the need to ensure the elections are conducted in peaceful, constructive and credible environment,&rdquo; Ndung&rsquo;u said.He said ICPC is ready to support the IEBC in taking steps to reinforce integrity in the electoral system. &ldquo;Information about these steps is not widely understood by many,&rdquo; he said.